
### 3. **Creating a GitHub Repository:**

1. **Create a New Repository:**
   Go to GitHub and create a new repository, for example, `simple-ai-chatbot`.

2. **Push Your Local Project to GitHub:**
   Once you have the files above set up locally, navigate to your project folder and initialize a Git repository.

   ```bash
   git init
   git add .
   git commit -m "Initial commit of simple AI chatbot"
   git branch -M main
   git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/simple-ai-chatbot.git
   git push -u origin main
